<h2>pinyin: Convert Chinese Characters into Pinyin, Sijiao, Wubi or Other
Codes</h2>
<p>Convert Chinese characters into Pinyin (the official romanization system for Standard Chinese in mainland China, Malaysia, Singapore, and Taiwan. See &lt;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pinyin">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pinyin</a>&gt; for details), Sijiao (four or five numerical digits per character. See &lt;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Four-Corner_Method">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Four-Corner_Method</a>&gt;.), Wubi (an input method with five strokes. See &lt;<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wubi_method">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wubi_method</a>&gt;) or user-defined codes.</p>
